</p><p><br />
</p><p>More generally, the difference of the squares of two numbers is the product of their sum and their difference. That is,<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle a^{2}-b^{2}=(a+b)(a-b)}">
